ocumentation for scrollback (and "no-scroll")...<br /><br />Note that scrollback hasn't actually gone away entirely - the original<br />scrollback supported by _hardware_ still exists.<br /><br />Of course, that's really just the old-fashioned text VGA console, but<br />that one actually scrolls not by moving any bytes around, but by<br />moving the screen start address. And the scrollback similarly isn't<br />about any software buffering, but about the ability of moving back<br />that screen start address.<br /><br />Do people use that? Probably not. But it wasn't removed because it<br />didn't have any of the complexities and bitrot that all the software<br />buffering code had.<br /><br />That said, I didn't check how much of the documentation is for the VGA<br />text console, and how much of it is for the actual software scrollback<br />for fbcon etc. So it is entirely possible that all the docs are about<br />the removed parts.<br /><br />              Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
